    "summary": "The 21st century is often described as the era of technology. Technological innovations have reshaped every sphere of human life, from communication and transportation to healthcare, governance, and commerce. In today’s knowledge-driven global economy, technology is considered a crucial indicator of national development. Countries that fail to adopt and integrate technological advancements struggle to compete economically and socially. Technology simplifies tasks, enhances productivity, increases efficiency, and saves time. It transforms traditional processes into faster, more reliable systems."
